name: float_f64_max_finite
description: |
  This is the largest finite binary64 value. Operations that round above this
  range may produce positive infinity, saturate, trap, or be evaluated at an
  extended precision before rounding. Pairing it with infinity targets overflow
  checks that rely on ordinary finite comparisons.
format: hex
decode-as: f64-le
pair:
  - with: positive-infinity.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f64"
  - "overflow"
  - "boundary"
---
ff ff ff ff ff ff ef 7f   # 0x7fefffffffffffff: maximum finite binary64
